    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-02-08T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-02-08T13:00:00-05:00" n="221"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d221">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">350/2–851: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Italy</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d221fn1">Repeated for information to <gloss
                            target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> as 694.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-02-08T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 8, 1951—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3437. Ital <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> informs <gloss target="#t_Dept1"
                        >Dept</gloss> Ital observer <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> has been
                    instructed press for full Ital participation <gloss target="#t_TC1">TC</gloss>
                    including right to vote. Ital Govt said to believe owing Ital non-membership
                        <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> although an administering power, new
                    situation exists which not contemplated when <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>
                    Charter adopted.</p>
                <pb facs="0317" n="295" xml:id="pg_295"/>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> informally explained that only ways in
                    which Ital participation with vote cld be achieved are (<hi rend="italic"
                    >a</hi>) Ital admission <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> or (<hi rend="italic"
                        >b</hi>) amendment Art 86 Charter in accordance Art 108. Neither these
                    courses feasible or likely be fruitful at this time; in any case <gloss
                        target="#t_TC1">TC</gloss> cannot act thereon. <gloss target="#t_TC1"
                        >TC</gloss> cld at most make recommendation to <gloss target="#t_GA1"
                        >GA</gloss>.</p>
                <p>Accordingly, <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> indicated to Ital <gloss
                        target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> US Del cld not support proposal for Ital vote
                    in <gloss target="#t_TC1">TC</gloss> but wld of course take position outlined
                    last sentence <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 3297 Feb 1.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> requests you informally convey our
                    thinking this matter to appropriate officials <gloss target="#t_FonOff1"
                        >FonOff</gloss>. You shld add to foregoing our thought that attempts force
                    either membership or Charter amendment issues at this time wld be ill-advised
                    and, apart from US inability support Ital, might well be counterproductive for
                    Ital, not only in <gloss target="#t_TC1">TC</gloss> but in more gen <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> context.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
